#   
def preprocess_text(text):
  ##   float      
  text = str(text)

  # 
  text.replace("\n", " ")

  #-> 
  text = text.lower()

  return text if text else None


#    
def del_space(text):
  text = ' '.join(text.split())
  return text

#
def text_tokenizer(data):
  doc = nlp(data)
  tokens = []
  for token in doc:
      tokens.append(token.text)

  #   
  result = []
  for w in tokens:
    if w not in stop_ita:
      result.append(w)
  return result

tokenized = []
for elem in range(len(data_df)):
  tokenized.append(text_tokenizer(data_df[" "][elem]))
print(tokenized)

import collections

# (ex. immagina -> immaginare)
def text_lemmatizer(data):
  doc = nlp(data)
  tokens = []
  for token in doc:
      tokens.append(token.lemma_)

  #  
  result = []
  for w in tokens:
    if w not in stop_ita:
      result.append(w)
  return result

stop_ita = set(stopwords.words("italian"))
print(stop_ita)

# 
for stopword in stop_ita:
    if stopword in counts.keys():
        del counts[stopword]

counts_df = pd.DataFrame(counts.most_common(),columns=['parola','count'])

from numpy.random import randint
import matplotlib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib import font_manager, rc
from PIL import Image
from wordcloud import WordCloud, STOPWORDS, ImageColorGenerator
mask = np.array(Image.open("/content/drive/MyDrive/  /flag.png"))

wc = WordCloud(prefer_horizontal=1.0,
               background_color="rgb(255,255,255)", mask=mask, color_func=ImageColorGenerator(mask),
               min_font_size = 2, # max_font_size = 100,
               max_words=150, width=2560, height=1707).generate_from_frequencies(counts) 

plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))
plt.imshow(wc, interpolation="bicubic")
plt.axis("off")
plt.savefig("/content/drive/MyDrive/  /wordcloud.png", facecolor="#FFFFFF", bbox_inches="tight")
plt.show()
